<div class="comment-wrapper"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8aa3a9da9a32d3e98805b4a5409e4cee?s=50"></div><header><strong>Case conventions for mixed-case words (like &quot;iPad&quot; and &quot;NaN&quot;)</strong> from <string>Anton Zhilin</string> &lt;antonyzhilin at gmail.com&gt;<p>May  5, 2016 at 06:00:00pm</p></header><div class="content"><p>Following my current cpp guidelines, I would suggest the following:<br></p><p>1. Make all letters of the abbreviation downcase<br>2. Make first letter uppercase if required<br></p><p>Examples: NanWrapper, getNan, nanGet, NextEmulator, emulateNext,<br>nextEmulate.<br></p><p>Although, this convention plays pretty hard on NeXT, I have to admit.<br></p><p>- Anton<br>-------------- next part --------------<br>An HTML attachment was scrubbed...<br>URL: &lt;https://lists.swift.org/pipermail/swift-evolution/attachments/20160505/0b81f405/attachment.html&gt;<br></p></div></li></ul></div>    </main>
